<h1>Learn to push it... to Heroku</h1>

<div class="col-md-4">
	<ol>
		<h3>Adjusting Gems</h3>
		<li>
			group :development, :test do
				gem 'sqlite3'
  			gem 'byebug'
  		end
  	</li>
		<li>
			group :production do
				gem 'pg'
				gem 'rails_12factor'
			end
		</li>
		<li>Run bundle, it pg doesn't install, run bundle --without production</li>
		<h3>Git</h3>
		<li>Initialize your git repo - git init</li>
		<li>git add .</li>
		<li>git commit -m "Commit message here"</li>
		<li>Create a Github repo</li>
		<li>Add the github repo remote - git remote add origin git@github.com:TheCoderFactory/push-it-heroku.git</li>
		<li>Push to your new repo - git push -u origin master</li>
		<h3>Heroku</h3>
		<li>Create a Heroku app</li>
		<li>Login to Heroku through your terminal - heroku login</li>
		<li>Add the Heroku remote - heroku git:remote -a appname</li>
		<li>Push to your heroku remote</li>
	</ol>
</div>

